In a bold brave move taken by the government, Kenya is locking its airspace to those intending to fly in or out to and from India by suspending all flights to and from the populous Asian country for a period of two weeks, beginning this Saturday. this is due to a surge in covid19 cases in the country. speaking in Taita Taveta county, health cabinet secretary mutahi kagwe said that the decision was arrived at after a crisis meeting held on Tuesday. KTN's health & science reporter Saada Hassan with the update.